                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="18009205" author="mkl" created="Wed, 23 Jul 2025 09:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, t&apos;s reasonable to check the sum of those &lt;b&gt;W&lt;/b&gt; values (in &lt;tt&gt;parse&lt;/tt&gt; a &lt;tt&gt;byte[]&lt;/tt&gt; as large as that sum is created), but IMO the proposed limit &lt;tt&gt;MAX_LINE = 1000000&lt;/tt&gt; still is too large; for most reasonable PDFs there hardly is reason to even have a two-digit sum, so a  &lt;tt&gt;MAX_LINE = 20&lt;/tt&gt; would be ok, too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Admittedly, there is no limit for the &lt;b&gt;W&lt;/b&gt; values in the spec, so &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;7 7 7&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; would be valid per se, but it would have quite a smell of a attempt to break some tools.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
